s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:6;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:15:\"structured data\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:28:\"https://aioseo.com/?p=152229\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:445:\"<p>Would you like to know how to add Local Business schema in WordPress? If you run a service-based or brick-and-mortar business, adding Local Business schema will help you rank for local searches and drive foot traffic to your business. In&#8230;</p>\nThe post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-add-local-business-schema-in-wordpress/\">How to Add Local Business Schema in WordPress</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"Kato Nkhoma\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:26483:\"<p>Would you like to know how to add Local Business schema in WordPress?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you run a service-based or brick-and-mortar business, adding Local Business schema will help you rank for local searches and drive foot traffic to your business.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In this article, we’ll show you how to add Local Business schema to your WordPress site, even if you don’t have any coding knowledge.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"is-layout-flow wp-block-group aioseo-table-of-contents has-theme-info-background-color has-background\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<p>In This Article</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-aioseo-table-of-contents\"><ul><li><a href=\"#aioseo-what-is-local-business-schema-markup\">What is Local Business Schema Markup?</a><ul><li><a href=\"#aioseo-why-local-business-schema-is-important\">Why Local Business Schema is Important</a></li></ul></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-how-to-add-local-business-schema-in-wordpress\">How to Add Local Business Schema in WordPress</a><ul><li><a href=\"#aioseo-step-1-install-all-in-one-seo-aioseo\">Step 1. Install All In One SEO (AIOSEO)</a></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-step-2-add-location-schema-single-location-business\">Step 2: Add Location Schema (Single Location Business)</a></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-step-3-add-location-schema-multiple-location-business\">Step 3: Add Location Schema (Multiple Location Business)</a><ul><li><a href=\"#aioseo-1-locations-permalink\">1. Locations Permalink</a></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-2-locations-category-permalink\">2. Locations Category Permalink</a></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-3-enhanced-search\">3. Enhanced Search</a></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-4-custom-admin-labels\">4. Custom Admin Labels</a></li></ul></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-step-4-add-opening-hours\">Step 4: Add Opening Hours</a></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-step-5-add-google-maps\">Step 5: Add Google Maps</a></li></ul></li></ul></div>\n</div></div>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"aioseo-what-is-local-business-schema-markup\">What is Local Business Schema Markup?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Schema markup, or structured data, is a semantic language that helps search engines better understand your content. It involves using tags that give search engines more context about your pages or posts.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Local Business schema, therefore, refers to the schema type you add to your website to help search engines better identify your business, the products or services you provide, and your location.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-aioseo-theme-notice-box\" role=\"alert\">\n<p>Note: Local Business schema markup is ONLY output in the homepage source code, as per Schema.org requirements.</p>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-why-local-business-schema-is-important\">Why Local Business Schema is Important</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The biggest advantage of adding Local Business schema to your site is it helps boost your local SEO. As a result, you get to rank for relevant local searches related to your business. Another reason is that it helps search engines generate rich snippets for your search listings. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"702\" height=\"416\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/local-business-schema-pizza-snippet.png\" alt=\"Local Business schema helps you  generate location specific rich snippets for your search listings.\" class=\"wp-image-155336\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/local-business-schema-pizza-snippet.png 702w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/local-business-schema-pizza-snippet-300x178.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/local-business-schema-pizza-snippet-600x356.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 702px) 100vw, 702px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Rich snippets are search listings that offer searchers more information, resulting in higher organic clickthrough rates (CTRs).</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Check out this step-by-step guide for other <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-add-rich-snippets-to-wordpress/\" title=\"How to Add Rich Snippets to WordPress (The Easy Way)\">tips on generating rich snippets</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"aioseo-how-to-add-local-business-schema-in-wordpress\">How to Add Local Business Schema in WordPress</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Ready to add Local Business schema to your site and boost your local SEO?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Let’s get started.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-step-1-install-all-in-one-seo-aioseo\">Step 1. Install All In One SEO (AIOSEO)</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The first step to adding Local Business schema to WordPress is installing a powerful SEO plugin like <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\" title=\"Pricing\">All In One SEO</a> AIOSEO.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"700\" height=\"311\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/aioseo.png\" alt=\"AIOSEO is the best plugin to help you know how to add local business schema.\" class=\"wp-image-151544\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/aioseo.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/aioseo-300x133.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/aioseo-600x267.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\" title=\"Pricing\">AIOSEO</a> is the best WordPress SEO plugin on the market. Over 3 million savvy website owners and marketers trust the plugin to help them dominate <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/what-are-serps/\" title=\"What Are SERPs (And Why Are they Important to SEO)?\">search engine results pages</a> (SERPs) and drive relevant traffic to their sites. This is because the plugin has many <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/features/\" title=\"Features\">powerful SEO features</a> and modules to help you optimize your website for search engines and users.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>One of the features many local businesses rave about is the Local SEO module.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>This powerful module is designed to help you rank your website and content for local searches, resulting in more business for your brand.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For step-by-step instructions on how to install AIOSEO, check out our <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/docs/installing-all-in-one-seo-pro/\" title=\"Installing All in One SEO Pro\">installation guide</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-step-2-add-location-schema-single-location-business\">Step 2: Add Location Schema (Single Location Business)</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Once you’ve installed AIOSEO, the next step to adding Local Business schema is to add your business and location information. To do that, go to the <strong>AIOSEO menu » Local SEO</strong>. This will open a page where you can input your location and business information.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"702\" height=\"182\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/local-business-schema-1.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-155353\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/local-business-schema-1.png 702w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/local-business-schema-1-300x78.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/local-business-schema-1-600x156.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 702px) 100vw, 702px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>One of the first things you’ll have to add is to indicate whether your business is a single or multiple-location business.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"702\" height=\"456\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/local-business-schema-multiple-locations.png\" alt=\"AIOSEO enables you to add schema for single and multiple locations.\" class=\"wp-image-155356\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/local-business-schema-multiple-locations.png 702w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/local-business-schema-multiple-locations-300x195.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/local-business-schema-multiple-locations-600x390.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 702px) 100vw, 702px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>If yours is a single-location business, leave the <strong>Multiple Locations</strong> toggle set to <strong>No</strong>.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can also choose whether you want your location information to be displayed as a:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>Gutenberg Block</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Shortcode</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Widget</li>\n\n\n\n<li>PHP code</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Next, add other business information like name, logo (image), business type, and address.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"702\" height=\"468\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/local-business-schema-business-info-1.png\" alt=\"You can add business information like name, logo (image), business type, and address\" class=\"wp-image-155358\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/local-business-schema-business-info-1.png 702w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/local-business-schema-business-info-1-300x200.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/local-business-schema-business-info-1-600x400.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 702px) 100vw, 702px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>You can also add other information like a map of your location (more on this in a moment), contact information, VAT and Tax IDs, payment information, and the areas you serve.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"702\" height=\"524\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/local-business-schema-business-info-2.png\" alt=\"You can also add other information like a map of your location, contact information, VAT and Tax IDs, payment information, and more.\" class=\"wp-image-155360\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/local-business-schema-business-info-2.png 702w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/local-business-schema-business-info-2-300x224.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/local-business-schema-business-info-2-600x448.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 702px) 100vw, 702px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>&nbsp;Once you’ve filled in these fields, click the <strong>Save Changes</strong> button.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"702\" height=\"371\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/local-business-schema-save-info.png\" alt=\" Once you’ve filled in your business information, click the Save Changes button\" class=\"wp-image-155362\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/local-business-schema-save-info.png 702w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/local-business-schema-save-info-300x159.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/local-business-schema-save-info-600x317.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 702px) 100vw, 702px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>AIOSEO will save this information to your Local Business schema.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-step-3-add-location-schema-multiple-location-business\">Step 3: Add Location Schema (Multiple Location Business)</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>If you run a multi-location business, you can add all your locations to your Local Business schema. To do so, you must set the <strong>Multiple Locations</strong> toggle to <strong>Yes</strong>.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"702\" height=\"445\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/local-business-schema-multiple-locations-1.png\" alt=\"You add Local Business schema for multiple locations, set the Multiple Locations toggle to Yes.\" class=\"wp-image-155364\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/local-business-schema-multiple-locations-1.png 702w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/local-business-schema-multiple-locations-1-300x190.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/local-business-schema-multiple-locations-1-600x380.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 702px) 100vw, 702px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Again, you can choose whether you want your location information to be displayed as a:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>Gutenberg Block</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Shortcode</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Widget</li>\n\n\n\n<li>PHP code</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>After clicking <strong>Yes</strong> on the <strong>Multiple Locations</strong> toggle, click on <strong>Save Changes,</strong> and AIOSEO will create a new post type called <strong>Locations</strong> which you’ll see in the WordPress menu.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"700\" height=\"544\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/local-business-schema-locations-wp-admin.png\" alt=\"When setting Local Business schema for multiple locations, AIOSEO will create a new post type called Locations which you’ll see in the WordPress menu.\" class=\"wp-image-155366\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/local-business-schema-locations-wp-admin.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/local-business-schema-locations-wp-admin-300x233.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/local-business-schema-locations-wp-admin-600x466.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>This is where you’ll add your different locations by clicking on the <strong>Add New</strong> option.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Doing so will open a page in editor mode, allowing you to add another location.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"701\" height=\"273\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/local-business-schema-sawgrass.png\" alt=\"Example of of a Locations page.\" class=\"wp-image-155367\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/local-business-schema-sawgrass.png 701w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/local-business-schema-sawgrass-300x117.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/local-business-schema-sawgrass-600x234.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 701px) 100vw, 701px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>You can then add an <strong>AIOSEO &#8211; Local Business Info</strong> block to pull your location data.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"701\" height=\"358\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/local-business-schema-location-block.png\" alt=\"Add an AIOSEO Local Business Info block.\" class=\"wp-image-155369\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/local-business-schema-location-block.png 701w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/local-business-schema-location-block-300x153.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/local-business-schema-location-block-600x306.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 701px) 100vw, 701px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>After adding your additional locations, you’ll also have to configure your advanced location settings, which are broken down into 4 sections:</p>\n\n\n\n<h4 id=\"aioseo-1-locations-permalink\">1. Locations Permalink</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>&nbsp;This is where you can view the permalink format that AIOSEO will use for your locations.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"702\" height=\"297\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/local-business-schema-permalink-settings.png\" alt=\"You can customize the Locations Permalink by checking the Use custom slug check box.\" class=\"wp-image-155371\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/local-business-schema-permalink-settings.png 702w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/local-business-schema-permalink-settings-300x127.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/local-business-schema-permalink-settings-600x254.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 702px) 100vw, 702px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>If you want to customize the <strong>Locations Permalink</strong>, check the <strong>Use custom slug</strong> check box. A field will be displayed where you can enter your custom slug to replace the word <strong>location</strong> in the locations permalink.</p>\n\n\n\n<h4 id=\"aioseo-2-locations-category-permalink\">2. Locations Category Permalink</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>The <strong>Locations Category Permalink</strong> field shows the permalink format All in One SEO will use for your location categories.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"702\" height=\"376\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/local-business-schema-location-category.png\" alt=\"Customize the Locations Category Permalink by checking the Use custom category slug check box.\" class=\"wp-image-155372\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/local-business-schema-location-category.png 702w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/local-business-schema-location-category-300x161.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/local-business-schema-location-category-600x321.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 702px) 100vw, 702px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>You can customize the <strong>Locations Category Permalink</strong> by checking the <strong>Use custom category slug</strong> check box. A field will be displayed where you can enter your own slug to replace the <strong>locations-category</strong> slug.</p>\n\n\n\n<h4 id=\"aioseo-3-enhanced-search\">3. Enhanced Search</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>Next, you’ll see the <strong>Enhanced Search</strong> setting. Setting it to <strong>Off</strong> means your locations won’t appear in search results on your site.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"702\" height=\"258\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/local-business-schema-enhanced-search.png\" alt=\"The Enhanced search function helps you control whether all other locations appear in search or not.\" class=\"wp-image-155377\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/local-business-schema-enhanced-search.png 702w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/local-business-schema-enhanced-search-300x110.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/local-business-schema-enhanced-search-600x221.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 702px) 100vw, 702px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>However, setting the toggle to <strong>On</strong> results in your locations being included in search results on your site. Switching the <strong>Enhanced Search</strong> toggle to <strong>On</strong> also displays an additional setting, the <strong>Enhanced Search – Excerpt</strong>. You can turn the toggle to <strong>On</strong> if you want location addresses to appear in search results on your site.</p>\n\n\n\n<h4 id=\"aioseo-4-custom-admin-labels\">4. Custom Admin Labels</h4>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Custom Admin Labels</strong> enable you to control what the menu item for <strong>Locations</strong> is called.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"702\" height=\"337\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/local-business-schema-custom-admin-labels.png\" alt=\"Custom Admin Labels enable you to control what the menu item for Locations is called.\" class=\"wp-image-155376\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/local-business-schema-custom-admin-labels.png 702w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/local-business-schema-custom-admin-labels-300x144.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/local-business-schema-custom-admin-labels-600x288.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 702px) 100vw, 702px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>If you want to call <strong>Locations</strong> something different in the WordPress Admin area, then enter the new single and plural labels here. For example, if we choose “Greater Florida” as our custom label and click <strong>Save Changes</strong>, that’s what we’ll have in the WordPress admin area instead of <strong>Locations</strong>.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"702\" height=\"319\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/local-business-schema-custom-label.png\" alt=\"If you want to call Locations something different in the WordPress Admin area, then enter the new single and plural labels here.\" class=\"wp-image-155378\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/local-business-schema-custom-label.png 702w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/local-business-schema-custom-label-300x136.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/local-business-schema-custom-label-600x273.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 702px) 100vw, 702px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-step-4-add-opening-hours\">Step 4: Add Opening Hours</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The next step to adding Local Business schema is to add your business hours. To do that, go to the <strong>AIOSEO menu » Local SEO » Opening Hours.</strong> This will open a window where you can add your opening hours.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"702\" height=\"549\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/local-business-schema-opening-hours-1.png\" alt=\"The Open Hours tab enables you to output Opening Hours schema markup.\" class=\"wp-image-155381\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/local-business-schema-opening-hours-1.png 702w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/local-business-schema-opening-hours-1-300x235.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/local-business-schema-opening-hours-1-600x469.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 702px) 100vw, 702px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Set the <strong>Show Opening Hours</strong> toggle to <strong>Yes,</strong> and you’ll be presented with options for displaying your opening hours. Again, you can use a Gutenberg block, short code, widget, or PHP code.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-aioseo-theme-notice-box\" role=\"alert\">\n<p>Note: Opening Hours Schema markup is ONLY output in the homepage source code, as per Schema.org requirements.</p>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<p>Next, you’ll see the <strong>Labels</strong> section. This is where you can set the text to be displayed when you’ve set opening hours for any day to either <strong>Open 24h</strong> or <strong>Closed</strong>.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"702\" height=\"393\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/local-business-schema-opening-hours-settings.png\" alt=\"You can configure the display settings of your Opening Hours. \" class=\"wp-image-155384\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/local-business-schema-opening-hours-settings.png 702w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/local-business-schema-opening-hours-settings-300x168.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/local-business-schema-opening-hours-settings-600x336.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 702px) 100vw, 702px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>If your business is open 24 hours, you can set the toggle to <strong>Open 24/7,</strong> and that’s it. You’ve added business hours to your Local Business schema.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>However, if your business has set operating hours, the next step is to choose whether to change the time format to <strong>24H format</strong>. To do that, set the <strong>Use</strong> <strong>24H format</strong> toggle to on.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Next, set your operating hours by clicking on the days and hours you’re open and those you’re closed.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"702\" height=\"412\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/local-business-schema-hours.png\" alt=\"Set your operating hours by clicking the days and hours you\'re open.\" class=\"wp-image-155383\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/local-business-schema-hours.png 702w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/local-business-schema-hours-300x176.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/local-business-schema-hours-600x352.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 702px) 100vw, 702px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Once you’re done, click <strong>Save Changes,</strong> and your operating hours will be set.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-step-5-add-google-maps\">Step 5: Add Google Maps</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The final step to setting your Local Business schema is <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-embed-google-maps-in-wordpress/\" title=\"How to Easily Embed Google Maps in WordPress\">adding Google Maps</a>, so you can visually display your location. To do that, go to the <strong>AIOSEO menu » Local SEO » Maps</strong>. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"702\" height=\"349\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/local-business-schema-google-api.png\" alt=\"AIOSEO allows you to add a Google Maps API key so you can embed Google Maps on your site.\" class=\"wp-image-155385\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/local-business-schema-google-api.png 702w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/local-business-schema-google-api-300x149.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/local-business-schema-google-api-600x298.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 702px) 100vw, 702px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>You’ll have to add a Google Maps API key in the <strong>API Key</strong> field for search engines to render your map.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For step-by-step instructions on adding a Google maps API key, <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/docs/how-to-create-a-google-maps-api-key/\" title=\"How to Create a Google Maps API Key\">check out this guide</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Once done, click <strong>Save Changes</strong>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>And that’s it!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You’ve now added Local Business schema to your WordPress site, complete with a visual map of your location.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>We hope this post helped you learn how to add Local Business schema in WordPress. You may also want to check out other articles on our blog, like <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-set-up-seo-for-different-languages-and-countries/\" title=\"How to Properly Set Up SEO for Different Languages and Countries\">how to set up SEO for different languages</a> and <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-easily-find-and-fix-orphan-pages-in-wordpress/\" title=\"How to Easily Find and Fix Orphan Pages in WordPress\">how to easily find and fix orphan pages in WordPress</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you found this article helpful, then please subscribe to our <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/c/AIOSEO\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"\">YouTube Channel</a>. You’ll find many more helpful tutorials there. You can also follow us on <a href=\"https://twitter.com/aioseopack\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"\">Twitter</a>, <a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/company/aioseo/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"\">LinkedIn</a>, or <a href=\"https://facebook.com/aioseopack/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"\">Facebook</a> to stay in the loop.</p>The post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-add-local-business-schema-in-wordpress/\">How to Add Local Business Schema in WordPress</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:70:\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-add-local-business-schema-in-wordpress/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:7;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:85:\"\n		\n		\n					\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n					\n			\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:58:\"How to Add Author Schema in WordPress (Beginner’s Guide)\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:138:\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-add-author-schema-in-wordpress/?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=how-to-add-author-schema-in-wordpress\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:65:\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-add-author-schema-in-wordpress/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Tue, 24 Jan 2023 15:51:25 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:5:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4:\"Blog\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"SEO Tips\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"author schema\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:20:\"author schema markup\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:24:\"how to add author schema\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:28:\"https://aioseo.com/?p=153737\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:419:\"<p>Would you like an easy way to add author schema in WordPress? Did you know you can click a few buttons to get author schema applied to all content on your site? The schema can even be automatically added to&#8230;</p>\nThe post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-add-author-schema-in-wordpress/\">How to Add Author Schema in WordPress (Beginner’s Guide)</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:15:\"Sherrie Gossett\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:24412:\"<p>Would you like an easy way to add author schema in WordPress?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Did you know you can click a few buttons to get author schema applied to all content on your site? The schema can even be automatically added to new posts that you create.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>This step-by-step tutorial will show you how to use a plugin to automatically add author schema to your WordPress posts.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>What you&#8217;ll need</strong>: The <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\" title=\"\">All in One SEO (AIOSEO) plugin</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"is-layout-flow wp-block-group aioseo-table-of-contents has-theme-info-background-color has-background\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<p>In This Article</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-aioseo-table-of-contents\"><ul><li><a href=\"#aioseo-what-is-author-schema\">What is Author Schema?</a><ul></ul></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-how-to-get-author-schema-added-automatically-to-posts\">How to Add Author Schema</a><ul><li><a href=\"#aioseo-step-1-download-the-all-in-one-seo-aioseo-plugin\">Step 1: Download the All in One SEO (AIOSEO) Plugin</a></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-step-2-view-your-posts-schema-settings\">Step 2: View Your Post&#8217;s Schema Settings</a><ul></ul></li></ul></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-for-advanced-users-custom-schema-markup-and-structured-data-testing\">For Advanced Users</a><ul></ul></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-whats-next\">What’s Next?</a></li></ul></div>\n</div></div>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"aioseo-what-is-author-schema\">What is Author Schema?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Author schema helps search engines identify the author of a web page. This code also helps Google differentiate between authors that have similar (or the same) names. (An author can be a person or an organization.)</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>An author&#8217;s <em>name</em> tells <em>readers</em> who wrote a page.</li><li>Author <em>schema</em> tells<em> search engines</em> who wrote the article and how they are related to other web entities, such as organizations, creative works, and websites, including <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-themes/social-media-cheat-sheet-for-wordpress/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" title=\"\">social media</a>.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Applying author schema to your articles and announcements is a best practice recommended by Google.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"aioseo-why-is-author-schema-important\">Why is Author Schema Important?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Article attribution has long been a common practice, but author schema goes beyond attribution.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Transparency</strong>: Providing author schema helps build a transparent web where users can identify the content source.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Helping readers and Google</strong>: Author schema done right, includes a URL that links to an identifying page. Google asks that such a URL be included so that they can &#8220;<a href=\"https://developers.google.com/search/docs/appearance/structured-data/article#author-bp\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"\">better understand who the author is</a>.&#8221;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>It’s helpful to hyperlink the author&#8217;s name on an article to a page that lists all articles written by that person for that site.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>This makes it easy for readers to discover new content that interests them. (The author schema we&#8217;ll cover in this article includes a URL.)</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Accurate search results</strong>: Having author schema applied to articles helps Google deliver relevant search engine results.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For example, a search for writer Irina Slav returns the author&#8217;s contributor page at OilPrice.com, her LinkedIn profile, and other sites she&#8217;s written for.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"625\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/irina-slav-author-1024x625.png\" alt=\"irina slav author schema example\" class=\"wp-image-153743\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/irina-slav-author-1024x625.png 1024w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/irina-slav-author-300x183.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/irina-slav-author-768x469.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/irina-slav-author-1536x938.png 1536w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/irina-slav-author-600x366.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/irina-slav-author-98x60.png 98w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/irina-slav-author-147x90.png 147w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/irina-slav-author.png 1758w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Is Author Schema a ranking factor?</strong> While author schema is not directly a ranking factor, poor quality content coupled with a lack of expertise or the absence of author information can harm your rankings.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>This is particularly true if any or all of your content is “YMYL” content.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-what-are-ymyl-and-e-a-t\">What are YMYL and E-A-T?</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>YMYL is an acronym coined by Google to stand for &#8220;Your Money or Your Life.&#8221; This content typically dispenses advice on major life decisions, like financial investments and trading, safety, or health.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Google has higher standards for these pages: &#8220;YMYL pages should come from reputable websites and the content should be created with a <em>high level of expertise and authority</em>.&#8221;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The search engine giant created a related guideline called E-A-T (Expertise &#8211; Authority &#8211; Trustworthiness).</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Browsing the E-A-T information in the<a href=\"https://static.googleusercontent.com/media/guidelines.raterhub.com/en//searchqualityevaluatorguidelines.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"\"> Google Search Quality Evaluator guidelines</a> shows that &#8220;expertise&#8221; need not be formal. Everyday experiences of people (like enduring a disease) are a type of expertise.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can communicate this expertise by adding bio information to your authors’ pages.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"aioseo-how-to-get-author-schema-added-automatically-to-posts\">How to Get Author Schema Added Automatically to Posts</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>By using a WordPress plugin, you can get author schema (also called &#8220;author markup&#8221;) automatically applied to your posts.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In our tutorial below, your WordPress posts will also automatically include a link to an author page. This is in keeping with Google&#8217;s recommendations.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Your author page will be a dedicated page listing all that author&#8217;s articles. Later in this tutorial, we&#8217;ll explain how to add an author bio to this page.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-step-1-download-the-all-in-one-seo-aioseo-plugin\">Step 1: Download the All in One SEO (AIOSEO) Plugin</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>As the first step, we recommend downloading the <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\">All in One SEO (AIOSEO) plugin</a>. It&#8217;s easy to use and includes everything you need to add author schema to a WordPress page.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>All that’s necessary is to install and activate the plugin. By default, it adds an &#8220;Article&#8221; schema to your WordPress posts, including the author schema.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Currently, more than 3 million people are using the plugin, and it has high ratings on WordPress.org.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"471\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/2-aioseo-homepage-1024x471.png\" alt=\"aioseo homepage\" class=\"wp-image-146993\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/2-aioseo-homepage-1024x471.png 1024w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/2-aioseo-homepage-300x138.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/2-aioseo-homepage-768x353.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/2-aioseo-homepage-600x276.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/2-aioseo-homepage.png 1390w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>This SEO plugin includes everything you need (other than content) to maximize search traffic to your site.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-step-2-view-your-posts-schema-settings\">Step 2: View Your Post&#8217;s Schema Settings</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>In the WordPress editor, navigate to a post.</p>\n\n\n\n<ol><li>In the upper right-hand corner, click on the <strong>AIOSEO button.</strong> That will open the AIOSEO settings.</li><li>Next, click on <strong>Schema</strong>.</li></ol>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"549\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/aioseo-settings-1024x549.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-153746\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/aioseo-settings-1024x549.png 1024w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/aioseo-settings-300x161.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/aioseo-settings-768x412.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/aioseo-settings-600x322.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/aioseo-settings-112x60.png 112w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/aioseo-settings-168x90.png 168w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/aioseo-settings.png 1198w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>You&#8217;ll see that the &#8220;Article&#8221; schema has been automatically applied to your post. (<em>Remember, this schema includes the author schema</em>.)</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"533\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/aioseo-schema-in-use-1024x533.png\" alt=\"aioseo article author schema in use\" class=\"wp-image-153750\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/aioseo-schema-in-use-1024x533.png 1024w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/aioseo-schema-in-use-300x156.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/aioseo-schema-in-use-768x400.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/aioseo-schema-in-use-600x312.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/aioseo-schema-in-use-115x60.png 115w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/aioseo-schema-in-use-173x90.png 173w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/aioseo-schema-in-use.png 1174w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>By default, AIOSEO applies the Article schema to all of your WordPress posts.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Note</strong>: The schema is code that is invisible to your readers. It&#8217;s for search engines like Google to read.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-step-3-optional-add-a-bio-to-the-author-page\">Step 3: (Optional) Add a Bio to the Author Page</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>After you add the AIOSEO plugin to your WordPress site, authors’ names will automatically be hyperlinked to an author&#8217;s page.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In WordPress, you can add a bio to this page if you like. This author&#8217;s page (or &#8220;bio page&#8221;) can link out to social media or other related sites, like an Amazon book page for the author.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>This also gives Google&#8217;s algorithm a deeper understanding of who the author is.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"304\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/wired-magazine-author-bio-1024x304.png\" alt=\"wired magazine author bio\" class=\"wp-image-153752\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/wired-magazine-author-bio-1024x304.png 1024w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/wired-magazine-author-bio-300x89.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/wired-magazine-author-bio-768x228.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/wired-magazine-author-bio-600x178.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/wired-magazine-author-bio-190x56.png 190w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/wired-magazine-author-bio-303x90.png 303w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/wired-magazine-author-bio.png 1409w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><em>A bio page doesn’t need much information to be useful or interesting. This bio page for a </em>Wired<em> magazine author links to his book. Below the bio, readers can see a list of his articles.</em></p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can also add a bio automatically to each <em>article</em> an author writes. Check out this beginner&#8217;s guide for adding an <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-tutorials/how-to-add-an-author-info-box-in-wordpress-posts/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" title=\"\">author box</a> in WordPress.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-step-4-optional-add-additional-schema\">Step 4: (Optional) Add Additional Schema</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>There are lots of schema markup types: author schema is just one.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>With AIOSEO, adding schema is as easy as clicking a button. You&#8217;ll fill out a form for some schema types like Recipe and Local SEO. Also easy.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Below we&#8217;ve listed some of the most popular schema types and instructions on adding them to a page using the AIOSEO plugin.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Note</strong>: Schema is not a ranking factor. But it can be vital for search engine optimization (SEO). Schema makes content eligible for display as a &#8220;rich snippet&#8221; in search results. Because rich snippets stand out visually, they can significantly boost your click-through rates (CTRs).</p>\n\n\n\n<h4 id=\"aioseo-how-to-schema\">How To Schema</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>Any &#8220;how to&#8221; post should have How To schema added to it. Follow <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/docs/setting-how-to-schema-markup-in-your-content/\">these easy instructions</a> for adding How To schema to your web page.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"280\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/how-to-schema-1024x280.png\" alt=\"howto schema example\" class=\"wp-image-153754\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/how-to-schema-1024x280.png 1024w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/how-to-schema-300x82.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/how-to-schema-768x210.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/how-to-schema-600x164.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/how-to-schema-190x52.png 190w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/how-to-schema-330x90.png 330w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/how-to-schema.png 1088w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><em>Adding How To schema makes your page eligible to be displayed with additional links.</em></p>\n\n\n\n<h4 id=\"aioseo-local-seo-schema\">Local SEO Schema</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>This is essential for local businesses. Local SEO includes information like opening hours, location(s), type of business, and VAT or TAX ID information.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Instructions for using AIOSEO to add Local SEO can be found <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/docs/local-business-seo-for-a-single-location/\">here</a> and<a href=\"https://aioseo.com/docs/local-business-seo-for-multiple-locations/\"> here</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"572\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/local-seo-1024x572.jpg\" alt=\"local seo example\" class=\"wp-image-153756\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/local-seo-1024x572.jpg 1024w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/local-seo-300x168.jpg 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/local-seo-768x429.jpg 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/local-seo-600x335.jpg 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/local-seo-107x60.jpg 107w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/local-seo-161x90.jpg 161w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/local-seo.jpg 1388w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><em>Local SEO helps searchers discover your business.</em></p>\n\n\n\n<h4 id=\"aioseo-product-schema\">Product Schema</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>Also essential: <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/what-is-google-merchant-center-and-how-you-can-use-it-to-drive-sales/\">Product Schema</a> (also called Google Merchant Center Listing Schema). This is for anyone who&#8217;s selling anything online.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"477\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/product-schema-1024x477.jpg\" alt=\"product schema rich snippet example\" class=\"wp-image-153758\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/product-schema-1024x477.jpg 1024w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/product-schema-300x140.jpg 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/product-schema-768x358.jpg 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/product-schema-600x280.jpg 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/product-schema-129x60.jpg 129w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/product-schema-193x90.jpg 193w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/product-schema.jpg 1180w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><em>These aren’t ads. They’re web pages with product schema added.</em></p>\n\n\n\n<h4 id=\"aioseo-knowledge-graph\">Knowledge Graph</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>An organization, business, or person may be featured in a Google Knowledge Panel. These panels draw their information from a database called Knowledge Graph.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Read our <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/docs/a-guide-to-schema-org-markup-for-rich-snippets/\">schema guide</a> to find out how to make your content eligible for display in a Knowledge Panel.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"379\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/jeff-lawson-knowledge-panel-1024x379.jpg\" alt=\"jeff lawson knowledge panel\" class=\"wp-image-153760\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/jeff-lawson-knowledge-panel-1024x379.jpg 1024w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/jeff-lawson-knowledge-panel-300x111.jpg 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/jeff-lawson-knowledge-panel-768x284.jpg 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/jeff-lawson-knowledge-panel-600x222.jpg 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/jeff-lawson-knowledge-panel-162x60.jpg 162w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/jeff-lawson-knowledge-panel-243x90.jpg 243w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/jeff-lawson-knowledge-panel.jpg 1385w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><em>Example of a knowledge panel in Google search results. This panel is about Jeff Lawson, CEO of Twilio.</em></p>\n\n\n\n<h4 id=\"aioseo-faq-schema\">FAQ Schema</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>Many small businesses use FAQ pages to answer searcher queries. And FAQs on other content pages can increase click-throughs and <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/conversion-tracking/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" title=\"\">conversions</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Find out how to add WordPress FAQ blocks <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-use-a-wordpress-faq-block-to-boost-seo-and-get-more-traffic/\">here</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"972\" height=\"326\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/faq-best-french-restaurants.png\" alt=\"faq schema example\" class=\"wp-image-153762\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/faq-best-french-restaurants.png 972w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/faq-best-french-restaurants-300x101.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/faq-best-french-restaurants-768x258.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/faq-best-french-restaurants-600x201.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/faq-best-french-restaurants-179x60.png 179w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/faq-best-french-restaurants-268x90.png 268w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><em>FAQ schema makes your FAQs eligible for display in search results. According to Milestone Research, FAQs have the highest click-through rates (CTRs) of all rich results.</em></p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"aioseo-for-advanced-users-custom-schema-markup-and-structured-data-testing\">For Advanced Users: Custom Schema Markup and Structured Data Testing</h2>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Webmasters and DIY coders</strong>: You can add <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-create-custom-schema-markup-in-wordpress/\">custom schema markup</a> to the AIOSEO plugin and save it as a template.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The plugin accepts JSON-LD, which is what Google recommends for schema markup. (You can use free online converters to change Microdata or RDFa into JSON-LD.)</p>\n\n\n\n<p>AIOSEO will flag any errors on your JSON-LD. In addition, you can run your custom Schema markup through Google&#8217;s Rich Results Test right inside WordPress. (Find out more about structured data testing tools <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-run-a-rich-results-test-in-wordpress/\">here</a>.)</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-aioseo-theme-notice-box\" role=\"alert\">\n<p>AIOSEO has a REST API that you can use to make alterations where no setting currently exists in the plugin. See our <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/docs/fetching-updating-aioseo-data-via-the-wordpress-rest-api/\">API documentation</a>.</p>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-customizing-author-schema-in-aioseo\">Customizing Author Schema in AIOSEO</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Here are some ideas for customizing the author schema in AIOSEO:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Adding multiple authors to an article</li><li>Including other properties.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>You can include properties related to the Schema.org &#8220;<a href=\"https://schema.org/Person\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"\">Person</a>&#8221; Type, such as:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>jobTitle</li><li>alumniOf</li><li>hasCredential</li><li>memberOf</li><li>worksFor</li><li>email</li><li>telephone</li><li>award</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Consider that <strong>alumniOf</strong> and <strong>hasCredential</strong>, would have obvious appeal for academic organizations and related non-profits.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>There are many creative possibilities here. Consider browsing Schema.org or the<a href=\"https://jsonld.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"\"> Steal Our JSON-LD</a> site for copy-paste code you can add as custom templates in AIOSEO. (Steal Our JSON-LD currently has a custom Article Schema type that includes editor, publisher, and word count.)</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Also note that:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Google accepts the<a href=\"https://developers.google.com/search/docs/appearance/structured-data/article#article-types\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"\"> <strong>sameAs</strong> property</a> in place of an author <strong>url</strong>. (AIOSEO uses the <strong>sameAs</strong> property to output all social network links.)</li><li>Schema.org states that the HTML 5 rel tag <strong>rel=&#8221;author&#8221;</strong> is equivalent to the Schema author property.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>And remember that you can customize elements of the Article Schema (parent to the Author Schema) too. See Schema.org for ideas, like:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>backstory</li><li>newsArticle</li><li>abstract</li><li>audio</li><li>citation</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"aioseo-whats-next\">What’s Next?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Listing the author of an article helps readers understand the source. Adding author schema can help Google understand the author&#8217;s identity across the web and the <em>authoritativeness</em> of your content.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>That can result in your article appearing in more search queries.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>We hope this post helped you learn how to add author schema to your WordPress content, the easy way.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can also check out our article on how to <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-boost-your-small-business-seo/\">boost your SEO without expert help</a> and our complete <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/blog-post-seo-checklist/\">blog SEO checklist</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you found this article helpful, then please subscribe to our <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/c/AIOSEO\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"\">YouTube Channel</a>. You’ll find many more helpful tutorials there. You can also follow us on <a href=\"https://twitter.com/aioseopack\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"\">Twitter</a>, <a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/company/aioseo/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"\">LinkedIn</a>, or <a href=\"https://facebook.com/aioseopack/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"\">Facebook</a> to stay in the loop.</p>The post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-add-author-schema-in-wordpress/\">How to Add Author Schema in WordPress (Beginner’s Guide)</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:62:\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-add-author-schema-in-wordpress/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\